Python library utilizing newer IR tools built into the Linux kernel (no LIRC package needed!).

Uses python 3 (written on 3.8)

1. Install ir-keytable, v4l-utils (for ir-ctl) and raspotify
2. Run "sudo chmod +x test-hook.sh"
3. Add "--onevent *path-to-this-repo*/test-hook.sh" to the OPTIONS= line in /etc/default/raspotify
4. Run "crontab -e" and add "@reboot python3 *path-to-this-repo*/src/main.py

